⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Guardian's Charge
node TGL · TGL · ⟦The Guardian's Charge:TGL:7120ed⟧

WHO   — The Guardian's Charge — the sacred calling
WHAT  — The Guardian's sole purpose and sacred charge — to penetrate Naju, defeat its defenders, and activate the alien world's own self-destruct, ending it before it reaches Earth.
WHERE — TGL · The Guardian Legend  Framework inputs: The Guardian Legend (Compile, NES 1988)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because a thing made for one purpose exists only to spend itself upon it; because the charge is not chosen but answered; because a world must be ended so the Earth may live, and the Guardian was called to be the one who ends it.
HOW   — By single-minded resolve — going down into Naju, defeating each defender that bars the way, and arming the self-destruct at the cost of all else — a calling carried through to its sacrifice and not laid down.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  This is what I am for — to go down, to end it, and not to turn back.

